MQTT is an OASIS standard messaging protocol for the Internet of Things (IoT)

https://mqtt.org/

It is designed as an extremely lightweight publish/subscribe messaging transport that is ideal for connecting remote devices 
with a small code footprint and minimal network bandwidth.

MQTT is the most commonly used messaging protocol for the Internet of Things (IoT).
MQTT stands for MQ Telemetry Transport. The protocol is a set of rules that defines how IoT devices can publish and subscribe to data over the Internet.

